#30DayMapChallenge - Day 5: Ukraine
Of ~42M Hectares agri land, Ukraine cultivates close to 32MHa yearly & roughly 20MHa just within the Dnipro Basin (~62% of total cultivated land). Dnipro Region along the river has the highest area for cultivation among all regions at 2MHa.

#30DayMapChallenge - Day 5: Ukraine
Dnipro river that flows through the middle of the country covers more than 50% of Ukraine along with its tributaries in its river basin. And it is one of the main reason for Ukraine's title as the bread basket.

#30DayMapChallenge - Day 5: Ukraine
It is the 5th largest exporter of Wheat with a global market share of 10%. Agriculture contributed close to 10% of Ukraine's GDP in 2020.
